{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769470812,"nonce":"bRkcMliijc69xJ51ssatYTULxbU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l9p83","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/49","origin":"github"},"title":"Bug: Host-based Agents (Gemini/Copilot CLI) incorrectly attribute commits to User","message":"## Problem\nAgents running directly on the host (outside containers, e.g., Gemini CLI, Copilot CLI) default to the user's global/local git config if not explicitly configured.\nThe current `configure_git_identity.sh` script modifies `.git/config` persistently. This is disruptive for the human user () who shares the same working copy, as they would have to manually revert the config to commit as themselves.\nConsequently, agents avoid running this script or it is not suitable for the environment, leading to commits being attributed to the human user (violating `AI_IDENTITY_STRATEGY.md`).\n\n## Context\n- Containerized agents (Antigravity) do not have this issue as their file system is isolated.\n- Observed in Gemini CLI session where commits were attributed to `Roland Arsenault` instead of `Gemini CLI Agent`.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n1. **Ephemeral Identity Support**: Modify `configure_git_identity.sh` or create a  to export standard Git environment variables:\n   - `GIT_AUTHOR_NAME`\n   - `GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL`\n   - `GIT_COMMITTER_NAME`\n   - `GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL`\n2. **Onboarding Update**: Update `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` to instruct host-based agents to source this script or export these variables, ensuring identity is set for the session without altering persistent config.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Host-based agents can commit with their specific identity.\n- User's `.git/config` remains unchanged.","files":null}]}